<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Paladin to marry a Nec?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Paragon">Paragon</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:02 p.m. 27/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Paladin to marry a Nec?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/the_rathe.cgi?read=155" TARGET=_self>Re: Paladin to marry a Nec?</A> (Dynar, Paladin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>I disagree; this is a feasible marriage. Firstly, does Everquest not describe Necromancer's view on death as it being nothing more than the release of life's energy? I don't think that it is fair to impose upon a player who wishes to RP *and* be a Necro that he must be evil. I personally roleplay a Necro that is merely powerhungry--there is a vast amount of life energy being released, and I choose to embrace it as reverance to the dead, and to bring back souls of the dead so that they may do themselves proud, even after the blood has stopped pumping through their vanes. True for all necros? No. Misunderstood by city guards? You betcha. BUT--I don't consider myself evil. I try my best to prove my deeds to the guards of every city I venture to, allowing my actions to speak louder than my appearances. Now, if there was a Paladin who could look past what I am, and who I was, I think it would be perfectly reasonable for a marriage to commence. I do, however, think that while RP'ing, the conflict between the differing views on death should come into play, although I do not think that this goes against any RP 'rules.' I also do not think EQ should do something about this as someone earlier suggested--why should they police the lives of everyone online?

<P>Paragon.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
